<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - FULLER 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS - INSTALL - OIL PUMP (IF
        EQUIPPED)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="1">
        <title>OIL PUMP (IF EQUIPPED)</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">From the rear of the transmission, position the oil pump into place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032f5">Figure 155</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the socket head shoulder bolt to secure the pump in place (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032f5">Figure 155</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>Overtightening the bolt could bind up the pump.</para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With a 6mm socket head driver, tighten the bolt to 27 to 31 Nm (20 to 23 ft-lbs) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13032f5">Figure 155).</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13032f5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg13/G13032F5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 155. Installing Oil Pump</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
